<%# app/views/trust_center/docs/ai-use.html.erb %>

<div class="trust-doc">
  <div class="trust-doc-header">
    <div class="trust-doc-breadcrumb">
      <%= link_to "Trust Center", trust_home_url, class: "trust-doc-breadcrumb-link" %>
      <span class="trust-doc-breadcrumb-sep">/</span>
      <span class="trust-doc-breadcrumb-current">AI Use Policy</span>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-title-row">
      <%= image_tag "logo.png", class: "trust-doc-logo", alt: "Workplace.io" %>
      <div class="trust-doc-title">AI Use Policy</div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-subtitle">
      How Workplace.io uses automated analysis to generate culture insights, how we limit exposure of sensitive data, and the guardrails
      we apply to reduce misuse. This page intentionally excludes proprietary model and taxonomy details.
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-updated">Last updated: <%= @trust_center_stamp %></div>
  </div>

  <div class="trust-doc-body">
    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">At a glance</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-bullets">
        <ul class="trust-doc-bullet-list">
          <li><strong>Purpose-limited:</strong> automated analysis is used to generate organizational insights and trends.</li>
          <li><strong>Short-lived content:</strong> message content is processed briefly for analysis and then removed.</li>
          <li><strong>Derived metadata retained:</strong> structured results and aggregates are retained to power reporting.</li>
          <li><strong>Guardrails:</strong> role-based access and acceptable-use restrictions reduce surveillance risk.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">What we mean by “AI”</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        Workplace.io uses automated classification and scoring techniques to map collaboration signals into structured, research-informed metrics.
        We do not disclose proprietary model architecture, training data, or internal signal taxonomy in public documentation.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">What automated analysis is used for</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        Automated analysis supports product features such as metric trends, aggregate summaries, and structured signal outputs used for reporting.
        It is designed for organization-level insight rather than individual monitoring.
      </div>

      <ul class="trust-doc-list">
        <li>Generate aggregate metrics and trends at the workspace and group level.</li>
        <li>Produce structured outputs used to power dashboards and comparisons.</li>
        <li>Support operational quality checks and consistency of reporting over time.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">Inputs and outputs</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        Automated analysis may temporarily process message content and related metadata needed for analysis. Outputs are structured results and
        aggregates used for reporting.
      </div>

      <ul class="trust-doc-list">
        <li><strong>Inputs (short-lived):</strong> message content and limited metadata required for analysis.</li>
        <li><strong>Outputs (retained):</strong> derived metadata (structured results) and aggregated reporting data.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="trust-doc-links">
        <%= link_to "Data Handling & Retention →", trust_doc_url_for("data-handling"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">Where inference runs</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        Classification and culture inference workloads run on AWS using Amazon SageMaker, separated from the application serving layer hosted
        on DigitalOcean. We restrict access paths and credentials used to operate these workloads.
      </div>

      <div class="trust-doc-links">
        <%= link_to "Architecture & Data Flow →", trust_doc_url_for("architecture"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;
        <%= link_to "Subprocessors →", trust_doc_url_for("subprocessors"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">Interactive chat (optional)</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        Workplace.io includes an optional interactive chat feature that helps users interpret dashboards and metrics. When used, this feature may
        send a user’s prompt and limited dashboard context to a third-party AI provider (currently OpenAI) in order to generate a response.
        This chat feature is separate from our culture classification system, which runs on AWS using Amazon SageMaker.
      </div>

      <ul class="trust-doc-list">
        <li><strong>User-initiated:</strong> chat runs only when a user submits a prompt or interacts with chat features.</li>
        <li><strong>Minimized context:</strong> we limit what is sent to what is needed to answer the user’s request.</li>
        <li><strong>Sensitive input:</strong> we recommend users avoid entering sensitive personal data into free-form prompts.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="trust-doc-links">
        <%= link_to "Subprocessors →", trust_doc_url_for("subprocessors"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">Guardrails and intended use</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        Workplace.io is intended to support organizational health insights. We encourage configurations and access patterns that reduce the
        risk of individual surveillance and misuse.
      </div>

      <ul class="trust-doc-list">
        <li><strong>Role-based access:</strong> administrative controls are restricted to authorized roles.</li>
        <li><strong>Aggregation:</strong> reporting emphasizes group/workspace-level results.</li>
        <li><strong>Customer control:</strong> admins choose which sources to connect and can disconnect integrations.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="trust-doc-links">
        <%= link_to "Acceptable Use (Culture Insights) →", trust_doc_url_for("acceptable-use"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>
        &nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;
        <%= link_to "Aggregation & Anonymity →", trust_doc_url_for("anonymity-aggregation"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-section">
      <div class="trust-doc-section-title">Quality and change management</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-text">
        We manage changes to scoring and outputs to preserve consistency and reliability. We perform evaluation and operational checks appropriate
        to the platform’s maturity and customer needs.
      </div>

      <div class="trust-doc-links">
        <%= link_to "Model Governance →", trust_doc_url_for("model-governance"), class: "trust-doc-link" %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="trust-doc-footer">
      <div class="trust-doc-footer-title">Questions about automated analysis?</div>
      <div class="trust-doc-footer-text">
        Contact us for procurement reviews or deeper discussion of safeguards and intended use.
      </div>
      <div class="trust-doc-footer-actions">
        <%= link_to "Contact Trust & Security", trust_doc_url_for("contact"), class: "trust-doc-button" %>
        <%= link_to "Back to Trust Center", trust_home_url, class: "trust-doc-button trust-doc-button--secondary" %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
